history.content: Weekly homework assignments in the beginning but they're very doable; I heard it lightens up around the middle of the semester when you're supposed to be working on your project. I'm taking it with a bunch of my friends who are seniors and none of us think it's a worthwhile class; maybe if we were sophomores or juniors, we'd be getting more out of the class.

children.subject: Is 169 a good class to prepare you for internships/look good when applying to internships (I haven't done an internship yet)?

history.content: Wondering if I can take 152 + 169 together. They're both listed as "heavy workload" classes but looking at the 169 website it seems doable. Also wondering if 169 is worth taking in general; I don't personally know anyone who's taken it or is planning to.
history.subject: How is the workload of 169?
